Report: act_report¶

Insights:¶

  1. The higher the favorite_count, the greater the numerator and denomintor ratings. Most of the them had a higher favorite_count, moderate numerator_ratings and greater denominator ratings. This means its was not all the time all being greatest. In conclusion therefore, any dog that has a higher favorite_count has a high rating.

  2. The ralationship between the p1_conf and p2_conf is normaly distributed. This means most of the dogs has an average p1_conf and p2_conf. A few had less p1_conf and p2_conf and a few also had hig p1_conf and p2_conf. This means the relationship between the p1_conf and the p2_conf is average.

  3. The relationship among the means of p1, p2 and p3 is moderate. Since their difference is not all that big. This is because their differences is not all that big, p2 had the greatest, p1 was middle and p3 had last. Although there are differences, but the relation is moderate.
